I've seen a *big* astronomical package which is more than 50% Fortran
(the rest being C) successfully built and run under Linux: it is
MIDAS (Munich Image and Data Analisys System), developed at ESO (Munich).
If you want info about it you may contact Carlos Guirao: cguirao@eso.org.
