From: fox@graphics.cs.nyu.edu (David S. Fox)
Subject: This is Not a Question.  (Is it?)
Date: 18 Oct 1993 12:39:30 GMT

It is unreasonable to exclude all questions from any newsgroup,
since questions arise as a result of almost any linguistic 
interaction.  What we need to do is distinguish between the
types of questions we are trying to direct to comp.os.linux.help
and the sorts of questions acceptable everywhere.  For example,
questions starting "How do I...?" usually belong in the help
group, but "How should we (re-design the schedular to eliminate
thrashing when running out of swap space)?" or "What do you think
of this idea (for re-designing the scheduler...)?" should be
acceptable in the development group.  Questions like "Do you
want me to (distribute my PCMCIA drivers)?" are acceptable anywhere.
My point is that the directive "Please don't post questions here"
is absurd.  These postings need to be re-thought and re-written.
--
-david --  fox@graphics.cs.nyu.edu

